              "createdAt": "2023-09-04T10:13:02Z",
              "body": "Pro for including the statement: It will keep some cranks away 😁\r\n\r\nI agree that this is not the right place for it. What about `NumberTheory.FLT.Basic`? Then we could have a few special cases like `NumberTheory.FLT.Three`, `NumberTheory.FLT.Four` and flt-regular could add its proofs to `NumberTheory.FLT.Regular`.\r\n\r\nWhen we actually formalise FLT, we can rethink the organisation, but I bet it's safe to say that won't happen in the next ten years 😉 ",
              "author": {
                "login": "YaelDillies"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "IssueComment",
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c5lt0Xz",
              "createdAt": "2023-09-05T12:15:14Z",
              "body": "I think @YaelDillies has listed some good reasons to add this statement. Let's start a directory in which we can collect some special cases of Fermat that are done (or will be done in the near future, such as the regular case).\r\n\r\nI also agree that `n` should be the first parameter.",
              "author": {
                "login": "jcommelin"
              }
